data.title: Steam powered giraffe?
data.meta_description: Friend of mine just shared this. I'm 8 years too late.
data.meta_site_name: Cakewalk Discuss | The Official Cakewalk by BandLab Forum
data.text:
That was very interesting! There's been a few, um, changes in the band since this video though... The two guys on the left are gone, I didn't even find a reference to the bass player, and the, er, "guy" on the right (the twin of the guy in the center) is now, officially, a girl named Isabella (or Bunny). I guess, if you're an android, it doesn't really matter much, does it? ?

8 hours ago, craigb said:

That was very interesting! There's been a few, um, changes in the band since this video though... The two guys on the left are gone, I didn't even find a reference to the bass player, and the, er, "guy" on the right (the twin of the guy in the center) is now, officially, a girl named Isabella (or Bunny). I guess, if you're an android, it doesn't really matter much, does it? ?

Well, how perfectly boring. I can't tell you how many times I've heard of bands breaking up because of this.

Even VH-1 "behind the music" wouldn't bother recycling this timeworn, threadbare trope of a narrative.

The guy on the far right who malfunctions, what's his name? I know stage name is Rabbit but what's his real name? His character has since been replaced by a woman and though there's many pictures of this guy there's no real name for him anywhere

4 hours ago, Christian Jones said:

The guy on the far right who malfunctions, what's his name? I know stage name is Rabbit but what's his real name? His character has since been replaced by a woman and though there's many pictures of this guy there's no real name for him anywhere

Same person. Now his, I mean her name is "Bunny" and they have officially changed genders as of 2016. Sorry, I thought I made that part clear...

2 hours ago, craigb said:

Same person. Now his, I mean her name is "Bunny" and they have officially changed genders as of 2016. Sorry, I thought I made that part clear...

No. Those are different people, the one in the video is a guy. I'm talking literally, not the role-playing or whatever. Anyway I found him, he's Chris Bennett, the guy on the right.

Wait, are you saying he changed genders in real life?

Edited February 18, 2020 by Christian Jones
